Seventeen people have been arrested in Thika Town and Limuru for operating illegal LPG refilling canters.Police said they recovered 448 assorted gas cylinders, five vehicles and other equipment used in the trade.In Thika Town s Makongeni area, the officers said they arrested seven suspects and seized 213 assorted filled cylinders, 156 empty ones, a tanker and two lorries.In Limuru, 79 cylinders, a tanker and two salon cars were seized and 10 suspects arrested.Officials from the Energy Regulation Commission (ERC) had marked the premises as illegal before detectives from the Special Crimes Prevention Unit carried out raids.Police said operations against the illegal operations were ongoing in major towns.